      xml:id="resources.information.concepts.design.patterns.classical.structural.flyWeight.introParagraph">

  The flyweight pattern is useful when you have a large number of objects for which a 
  significant amount of the state is generic across all its instances, and where the 
  non-generic part of the state can be largely calculated from a few parameters.
</para>